From Steve Alexander Subject Re Compiling mh and xmh on SCO In article Jesse Asher writes I'm trying to get MH compiled and then xmh and I'm having some I've got mh using gcc on SCO My MH file is listed Does anyone have any suggestions on what I can add to get it to compile Here's the one that I used Id MH v sources Exp SCO bin usr local bin bboards on etc usr local lib mh mail usr spool mail mailgroup mail ldoptlibs lsocket lcrypt i mandir usr man cc gcc ccoptions traditional manuals none chown bin chown mts sendmail smtp pop on debug off sharedlib off signal void sprintf int options ATTVIBUG BIND DPOP DUMB RENAME SOCKETS VSPRINTF FCNTL MHE MHRC MIME MORE ' usr bin more ' POPSERVICE ' ' RPATHS FOLDPROT ' ' MSGPROT ' ' SBACKUP ' ' SHADOW curses lcurses ltermcap ranlib off You may want to use a different locking style my mailbox is mounted over NFS so I use fcntl style I also applied the following tweak to sbr src public mh sbr Tue Dec sbr Tue Apr include sys include sys endif if defined defined ncr include endif include sys include sys endif if defined defined ncr defined define MAXPATHLEN include endif That took care of everything but the man pages which I installed by Good luck Steve Steve Alexander Lachman Technology FAX sun ico laidbak stevea